<p>So it was necessary to use a recursive exploration of the document looking for string data to gather the text to process (<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">b_get_documents_topics.py</code>).</p>

<p>Also the use of a custom collection of stop words was necessary since the default list from NLTK was’t catching “thou” for example and also some words like “footnote” needed to be discarded.</p>

<p>With all this adjustments we could get our first topic models:</p>

<p>(1) 5ef89a6c56c1086443e21a92	Ktav Pub. House, NY, 1974	Major Themes in Modern Philosophies of Judaism</p>

